# General functioning

Each user will access the platform by using his/her credentials and on the same platform as the others. 

## User Interface

DINO can be accessed by two different kinds of users: “admin-user” and “collector-user”. They are linked to different duties and can visualise different sections of the platform. 

Hence, after logging-in, the user will visualise the following page. 

![][image2]

| Image 1\. Dashboard |
| :---- |

Different selectors are available (see dots in Image 1):

1. ⇓ Version Update. Whenever a new version of the application is released, an icon appears in the top right-hand bar allowing you to download the update.  
2. Light/dark mode. Allows you to change the viewing mode of the interface between light (left image) and dark (right image). 

![][image3]![][image4]

3. "i" Display the version number of DINO, Angular, Ajf and RxDb. In case of discrepancies with some colleagues, you can check that you are using the same version of the app.  
4. "?" Learn about DINO. This button by default redirects to the site dedicated to the application, but can be customised according to specific requirements.  
5. Synchronisation indicator. The two rotating arrows indicate that the system is synchronising with the central server and that locally collected or modified data are not yet synchronised. When the two arrows are stopped, the system is synchronised.   
6. Notifications. See specific section.   
7. Language selector. It is possible to change the working language.   
8. Username. The username is displayed. By clicking on the name, it is possible to change the password. 

![][image5]

| Image 2\. Edit password and DINO Theme |
| :---- |

9. Side menu. The side menu gives access to different features of the platform. The features are not the same for all users. The administrator can access all the features. Other users, in general, will have less functionality.   
10. Expansion side menu. The side menu can be displayed with only the icons.

The user who logged-in through the admin-profile visualises the whole menu displayed in the picture above, which includes the following sections: 

1. Dashboard  
2. Forms  
3. Reports  
4. Aggregation  
5. Metrics  
6. Users  
7. Translation
